[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating ClassInjection Issues**\n\nI’m taking a closer look at the current method that involves creating a ModuleLayer with the blockhound jar as an automatic module. When it loads the NexusAccessor class, its static initialization triggers a CreationAction. This process uses ClassInjector via reflection, but the SecurityManager denies ReflectPermission. \n\nI realize I might need to force injection failure more effectively by setting the system property `net.bytebuddy.nexus.disabled`. I also wonder about inspecting ClassInjector dispatchers and its relation to defineClass permissions in Java 21.\n\n**Analyzing ClassInjection Dynamics**\n\nI'm considering how the isolated loader operates. If I'm injecting into a system where Nexus is already loaded, it seems that the dispatcher’s findClass method might not require a define or injection. Maybe if Nexus is already in the system, it no longer triggers suppressAccessChecks? \n\nHowever, the CreationAction initializes the dispatcher, which could invoke suppressAccessChecks. I wonder if the failure occurs in the ClassInjector.UsingReflection constructor. I need to check line 237 to see if it includes injection and any exception handling that's happening.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0a4967bdb0d2adc6016a293293ec7c8193b702c2c035bc7443\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKTLAaJ826YxBmPEFlseP4VzOKXVFmhJJ8tMWhaPEnq7thqvd19A2nb0rrrHwTxm3xk6u_x0SC_eJ3h5vzgujT6DruxJ1yVYPdG4V3WB3H7LhrAeCMrpHNAslX-4ZSsVRmBfCDrGTHxFXarfg5gjEQ126MfZ6z5UOBcNPAEeEeDS_vn1Ip4AdObSrQe-KA5C5xQy3kO-m13wxUSM1lduX7XcpvwJfXUyrSNRrH3FPEYxc61e1KMiM9PhPhA3FdN9w4fJRskOgBg90KT7PTsC1d3NdRRtpkagOl7RsQxMDRkgDbhus74xDGw-p9C_3U8jtRQzePhJEgBzuKRNtPhSFLE_QCRCJJ9ISly9PIYKL6jFVs-op4IX9OrcDHF7L2z2UofiLX61_GhhppyWGbtX-_qtoBfpkLhevj9aup89DQ_hEFZo1B79LAzavr6FiBzUhIN0Ohi4kZ11UnTvrtYOY0d3YMvhlZsBO9cfp7r_kpPzomRGV491li8M8pgT