ers a CreationAction. This process uses ClassInjector via reflection, but the SecurityManager denies ReflectPermission. \\n\\nI realize I might need to force injection failure more effectively by setting the system property `net.bytebuddy.nexus.disabled`. I also wonder about inspecting ClassInjector dispatchers and its relation to defineClass permissions in Java 21.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing ClassInjection Dynamics**\\n\\nI'm considering how the isolated loader operates. If I'm injecting into a system where Nexus is already loaded, it seems that the dispatcher’s findClass method might not require a define or injection. Maybe if Nexus is already in the system, it no longer triggers suppressAccessChecks? \\n\\nHowever, the CreationAction initializes the dispatcher, which could invoke suppressAccessChecks. I wonder if the failure occurs in the ClassInjector.UsingReflection constructor. I need to check line 237 to see if it includes injection and any exception handling that's happening.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JjpDVyD5Zx8oi2ZYC6ELQ7Su|fc_0a4967bdb0d2adc6016a2932c06a7c8193b07bc917bd76560a", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/NexusAccessorInnerDispatcherInnerCreationActionTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.lang.reflect.ReflectPermission;\nimport java.lang.module.Configuration;\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleFinder;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.util.Set;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.ReflectPermission;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLClassLoader;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\n"}, {"oldText": "            registerInitializerThroughSystemNexus();\n            createAccessorWhenNexusClassIsAlreadyAvailableFromSystemClassLoader();\n", "newText": "            createAccessorWhenNexusClassIsAlreadyAvailableFromSystemClassLoader();\n            registerInitializerThroughSystemNexus();\n"}, {"oldText": "        Path blockhoundJar = Path.of(NexusAccessor.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource().getLocation().toURI());\n        ModuleFinder finder = ModuleFinder.of(blockhoundJar);\n        String moduleName = finder.findAll().iterator().next().descriptor().name();\n        Configuration configuration = ModuleLayer.boot().configuration()\n                .resolve(finder, ModuleFinder.of(), Set.of(moduleName));\n        ModuleLayer layer = ModuleLayer.boot()\n                .defineModulesWithOneLoader(configuration, ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader());\n        SecurityManager originalSecurityManager = System.getSecurityManager();\n        boolean securityManagerInstalled = false;\n        try {\n            try {\n                System.setSecurityManager(new DenyByteBuddyClassInjectionSecurityManager());\n                securityManagerInstalled = true;\n            } catch (UnsupportedOperationException exception) {\n                assertThat(NexusAccessor.isAlive()).isTrue();\n                return;\n            }\n            Class<?> isolatedAccessorType = layer.findLoader(moduleName).loadClass(NexusAccessor.class.getName());\n            MethodHandle isAlive = MethodHandles.publicLookup()\n                    .findStatic(isolatedAccessorType, \"isAlive\", MethodType.methodType(boolean.class));\n\n            assertThat((boolean) isAlive.invoke()).isTrue();\n        } finally {\n            if (securityManagerInstalled) {\n                System.setSecurityManager(originalSecurityManager);\n            }\n        }\n", "newText": "        Class.forName(\n                \"reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.dynamic.Nexus\